reviews.review:
The title was a complete LIE. Should have been named: Rise of the Legend Of Skywalker.
This movie was an amalgam of Empire Strikes Back anf Return of the Jedi.  And for both these reasons, I blame J.J. Abrams for being lazy and telling the same story with different characters.
And since Disney owns both Star Wars and Marvel, they didnt think anyone would notice copying the final fight scene in Endgame but use Rey and Palpatine.  Pathetically lazy.
The story was easy enough to follow. even if you didn't see all the story.  Graphics were amazing!

Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker is a great movie that ties together all of the most important themes while completing a brilliant interleaved narrative composition across the 3 collections of original movies, prequels and sequels leading to this 9th and final ending which answers all of the most important questions while delivering an amazing climactic ending that is both awe-inspiring and engaging and more importantly thought provoking and as relevant today as it was "A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away."

I loved the movie. I especially liked Kylo turning to the light after being killed by Rey and then forced-healed back to life. He had to die to become Ben again. That was nice. Leia being trained by Luke was epic! One thing that I would have liked to have seen was a flash forward beyond the ending Tatooine scene showing Rey heading a new Jedi academy but it worked.
Worst of the 9, acting and story felt bleak and uninteresting, even the big reveals felt a bit forced.
Loved how things were all tied together!  Learning Reys heritage!  And...  its a Star Wars movie, which I would always give two-thumbs up!!
It was amazing but i was expecting to see  baby yoda n didn't..other than that awesome !!
Loved it, JJ really did well with what he had
Entertaining. Acting not stellar. More of the same.
Very entertaining. They did well with rolling the story together now. Great action. Good story line. Just all around good time! Let go of your stubborn old ways and embrace the force!
